args: The village... What happened to it?!

A detachment of imperials attacked it
while you were fighting in the rearguard to
secure our retreat. By the time we returned
here ourselves, it was already too late.
We drove off the occupying imperial force,\nbut the damage to the village is severe.\nWe have no choice but to abandon it.
After I took on the role of holding back\nthe enemy to buy time to retreat...
The Lake Deira front line\nHours prior

Advance, loyal soldiers of the Other!
Bring down the hammer of his judgment
upon those who would rise against our
mighty Dyrenell Empire!
Damn, look at their numbers...\nWe're going to be overwhelmed!

A large number of enemy reinforcements
have appeared to the northeast, sir!
Requesting immediate reinforcements
to prevent the collapse of the front lines!
The imperial army appears to be\napproaching from the south, as well.\nWhat will our course be, Alberius?
We must withdraw. I want everyone to\nfollow Midgardsormr through the forest\nto the west and make for our base.
I will take up the rear and stop the enemy\nin their tracks. I will protect you all!
I know better than to try and sway you\nwhen your mind is decided. But I must\nwarn you, Alberius: Do not die on us.
I've not plans of doing so today.
The allied army will proceed through the\nwoods west of this location and withdraw\nto our garrison. All troops, follow me!
Time for me to be off.
Come at me, Imperial scum! Haaah!
Blimey, this guy's attackin' us all on his\nlonesome! Must be that Alberius dog\nwe've heard so much about!
He's a bloody idiot with a death wish,\nso let's grant it and go home already!
I shall take you all on at once!
What the...? He's just one man!\nHow can this be happening?!
This guy ain't human—we brought enough\nsoldiers to take out an entire CITY!
Not human? Heh. A fitting turn of phrase.
Cardinal Lambert...\nOr should I say, Morsayati?!

It has been some time, Alberius.
As the chosen hero of the sacred sword,
word of your commendable deeds has
found its way to me.
Then prepare to witness my deeds\nfirsthand, and know they will be\nthe final thing you ever see!
Aaaaah ha ha ha! Wonderful!\nThe hero has added comic timing\nto his list of meritorious traits!
Damnation! He killed the hero in one blow!
It matters not what caliber of hero you are;\nin the end, you are still a mere human.\nOpposing me was folly from the start.
You live? Fascinating. Well, no matter.\nThere won't be a second time.
You're right—because there's no way I'll\nlet you hit me with that again! Haaaah!

Heh, I see ＂hero＂ is not merely a title.
Your sword might even reach me
someday...but that just makes you all the
more pitiable.

Your power has begun to transcend human
limits. You are deviating from the way of
this world, and transforming into a being
of...this side.
Heh heh heh. Let us see now if you are\na hero for true. Go, my servants!
Has the truth begun to sink in now, hero?\nDo you see how very alone you are?
You may have thought to fight alongside\nyour comrades, but such notions are\nnaught but a fevered delusion.
Then look about you. Do you see anyone?\nAny hide or hair of comrades with whom\nyou could stand together?
None of the fellows you so desperately try\nto protect can keep up with your strength.
Have you not realized it in your heart?\nThe comrades fighting alongside you are\nnothing more than an impediment!
Enough of your pretensions, Morsayati!\nI have defeated all of your minions,\nand now your turn has come!
Do you really believe that trifling number\nof pawns was my final gambit?

This is the difference between us:
I am o'erflowing with minions such that
I can use them and toss them aside,
while you are utterly alone.
It would be a simple matter indeed to set\nmy fiends upon you and watch them put\nyou in the ground, but I will beg off.
What is your game here, devil?
Surrender to me, solitary hero.\nSurrender...and then serve me.
You know the answer without my\neven having to speak the words!
You would refuse readily now, perhaps.\nBut next time, who can say?
You will come to learn the extent to which\nhumans are selfish, foolish creatures.
In the near future, you will be betrayed\nby humans and have them reject you.\nSuch is the fate of all with great power.

Heh heh. What a spectacle it will be to
see what one extolled as a hero chooses.
I look forward to the next opportunity
to speak with you.

At any rate, I am relieved to see you safe.
You must be tired—and while the village
has been destroyed, we still have a
provisional barracks at the ready.
It's Alberius! The hero who protects us all!
Why didn't you protect my dad?!
Dad said you were amazing! He said\nyou'd beat the Other and save everybody!
But now he's gone! Why didn't\nyou save him?! Why?!
You! You were supposed to protect\nour village! Why didn't you?!
We only got attacked because of you!\nBetter that you had never come!

I'm sorry, everyone. I thought I could save
you all, but I wasn't strong enough.
And now you are paying the price
for that failure.
I swear to you this: I WILL make amends.\nPray just give me a little time.
It is unwise of you to apologize to them.\nDoing so only solidifies the false notion\nthat you are somehow to blame.

The villagers are caught up in their
emotions now, but with time, they will
regain their normal sense of judgment.
You need not shoulder that guilt.
You will come to learn the extent to which\nhumans are selfish, foolish creatures.
In the near future, you will be betrayed\nby humans and have them reject you.\nSuch is the fate of all with great power.
...It's the fate of all with great power,\nperhaps.
Fate? Just what do you mean?
My apologies; I am tired, and my mind\ngoes where it will. I'll go get some rest\nin those barracks you mentioned.
Something is amiss with you, Alberius...
